T1  - Comment: Businessmen Must Get Active in Politics
AU  - Grunewald, Donald
Y1  - 1965/03/01
PY  - 1965
DA  - 1965/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255133
DO  - 10.5465/255133
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 50
EP  - 52
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article explains why businessmen in the United States must become active in politics. The author outlines various talents that businessmen can contribute to the government and reasons behind the relationship between government and business enterprises. An overview of the importance of political action and ways businessmen can be active in politics is provided. A discussion is presented about incentives and methods used by corporations in order to encourage and promote political activity among businessmen.
AB  - The article explains why businessmen in the United States must become active in politics. The author outlines various talents that businessmen can contribute to the government and reasons behind the relationship between government and business enterprises. An overview of the importance of political action and ways businessmen can be active in politics is provided. A discussion is presented about incentives and methods used by corporations in order to encourage and promote political activity among businessmen.
