TY  - JOUR
T1  - A New Look At The Organizational Implications of Automation
AU  - Lipstreu, Otis
AU  - Reed, Kenneth A.
Y1  - 1965/03/01
PY  - 1965
DA  - 1965/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255129
DO  - 10.5465/255129
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 24
EP  - 31
VL  - 8
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article investigates the organizational changes brought about by the introduction of automation technology in a baking plant. Information related to the impact of automation on the amount of supervisory responsibility and the plant's ratio of supervisors to workers is presented. A discussion is presented about the impact of automation on the plant's labor force. The study found that while automation allows for more efficient production of goods, it increases the work level of supervisors and managers.
AB  - The article investigates the organizational changes brought about by the introduction of automation technology in a baking plant. Information related to the impact of automation on the amount of supervisory responsibility and the plant's ratio of supervisors to workers is presented. A discussion is presented about the impact of automation on the plant's labor force. The study found that while automation allows for more efficient production of goods, it increases the work level of supervisors and managers.
